.SH SHMagPowerSpectrum
Compute the power spectrum of the magnetic field given the Schmidt
seminormalized magnetic potential spherical harmonic coefficients.
.SH Usage
call SHMagPowerSpectrum (\f[CR]cilm\f[R], \f[CR]a\f[R], \f[CR]r\f[R],
\f[CR]lmax\f[R], \f[CR]spectrum\f[R], \f[CR]exitstatus\f[R])
.SH Parameters
.TP
\f[CR]cilm\f[R] : input, real(dp), dimension (2, \f[CR]lmax\f[R]+1, \f[CR]lmax\f[R]+1)
The Schmidt seminormalized spherical harmonic coefficients of the
magnetic potential.
.TP
\f[CR]a\f[R] : input, real(dp)
The reference radius of the magnetic potential spherical harmonic
coefficients.
.TP
\f[CR]r\f[R] : input, real(dp)
The radius to evaluate the magnetic field.
.TP
\f[CR]lmax\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The maximum spherical harmonic degree to calculate the power spectrum.
.TP
\f[CR]spectrum\f[R] : output, real(dp), dimension (\f[CR]lmax\f[R]+1)
The power spectrum of the magnetic field.
.TP
\f[CR]exitstatus\f[R] : output, optional, integer(int32)
If present, instead of executing a STOP when an error is encountered,
the variable exitstatus will be returned describing the error.
0 = No errors; 1 = Improper dimensions of input array; 2 = Improper
bounds for input variable; 3 = Error allocating memory; 4 = File IO
error.
.SH Description
\f[CR]SHMagPowerSpectrum\f[R] will calculate the power spectrum of the
magnetic field at radius \f[CR]r\f[R] given the magnetic potential
Schmidt seminormalized spherical harmonic coefficients \f[CR]cilm\f[R]
evaluated at radius \f[CR]a\f[R].
For a given degree \f[CR]l\f[R], this is explicitly calculated as (Lowes
1966):
.PP
\f[CR]S(l) = (l+1) (a/r)**(2l+4) Sum_{m=0}\(hal [ cilm(1, l+1, m+1)**2 + cilm(2, l+1, m+1)**2 ].\f[R]
.SH Reference
Lowes, F. J., Mean\-square values on sphere of spherical harmonic
fields, J. Geophys.
Res., 71(8), 2179, 1966.
